USER='105933'








Parent Borrower is a leading marketer and manufacturer of healthy/natural and indulgent specialty snack food brands. We operate in two segments: (1)&nbsp;frozen products and (2)&nbsp;snack products. The frozen products segment includes frozen fruits
 vegetables
 beverages
 blends
 and frozen desserts for sale primarily to groceries
 club stores and mass merchandisers. All products sold under our frozen products segment are considered part of the healthy/natural food category. The snack products segment includes potato chips
 kettle chips
 potato crisps
 potato skins
 pellet snacks
 sheeted dough products
 cereal
 popcorn
 and extruded products for sale primarily to snack food distributors and retailers. The products sold under our snack products segment includes products considered part of the indulgent specialty snack food category
 as well as products considered part of the healthy/natural food category. We also manufacture private label snacks for certain grocery retail chains and co-pack products for other snack and cereal manufacturers.

D489864 &#147;The ornamental design for a snack food
 as   shown and described.&#148;











May&nbsp;18

Inventure Foods
&nbsp;Inc.



We have patent pending technology to apply nutrients   sourced from fruits and vegetables to boost the nutrition level in our fortified   fruit products.&nbsp; In 2014
 we introduced&nbsp;Rader Farms&#174;&nbsp;Fruit   PLUS Vitamins&#153;
 the first-ever fortified whole frozen fruit product.&nbsp;   Using proprietary technology and topical nutrients sourced from whole fruits   and vegetables
&nbsp;Fruit PLUS Vitamins&nbsp;builds on naturally-occurring   vitamins found within whole strawberries
 blueberries and blackberries and   boosts the nutrition level with five additional vitamins: B1
 B6
 D
 E and K.







Serial No. 14/190
557



February&nbsp;26
 2014

Parent Borrower is a leading marketer and manufacturer of healthy/natural and indulgent specialty snack food brands. We operate in two segments: (1)&nbsp;frozen products and (2)&nbsp;snack products. The frozen products segment includes frozen fruits
 vegetables
 beverages
 blends
 and frozen desserts for sale primarily to groceries
 club stores and mass merchandisers. All products sold under our frozen products segment are considered part of the healthy/natural food category. The snack products segment includes potato chips
 kettle chips
 potato crisps
 potato skins
 pellet snacks
 sheeted dough products
 cereal
 popcorn
 and extruded products for sale primarily to snack food distributors and retailers. The products sold under our snack products segment includes products considered part of the indulgent specialty snack food category
 as well as products considered part of the healthy/natural food category. We also manufacture private label snacks for certain grocery retail chains and co-pack products for other snack and cereal manufacturers.

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;2.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Product Recall&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On April&amp;nbsp;23
 2015
 we announced a voluntary product recall of certain varieties of the Company&amp;#x2019;s Fresh Frozen&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:6.5pt;&gt;TM&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; line of frozen vegetables
 as well as select varieties of our Jamba&amp;#xAE; &amp;#x201C;At Home&amp;#x201D; line of smoothie kits because the Jefferson
 Georgia facility tested positive for Listeria monocytogenes.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The impacts recorded in our consolidated statement of operations attributable to the recall for the year ended December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015 are summarized as follows (in thousands):&lt;/font&gt;

 including product expected to be returned from customers and consumers
 partially offset by recall-related insurance recoveries.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Through December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015
 the Company has incurred an estimated $19.1 million of product recall charges.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As of December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015 we do not anticipate any additional product recall charges.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Additionally
 during the year ended December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015
 the Company incurred approximately $2.2 million of incremental production costs as a result of utilizing co-packers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;These charges were partially offset by recall-related insurance recoveries of $4.2 million.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

 general and administrative costs consists of approximately $2.2 million for the year ended December&amp;nbsp;26

			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;Amount reflects a $9.3 million impairment charge recorded to write-off the carrying value of the Fresh Frozen &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;customer relationships intangible asset.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div style=width:100%&gt;&lt;table style=width:100%; cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td style=width:36pt;&gt;&lt;p style=width:36pt;font-size:0pt;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td valign=top align=left style=width: 18.00pt; display: inline;&gt;
			&lt;p style=font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;&gt;
				&lt;font style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size:10pt;;&gt; (4)&lt;/font&gt;

			&lt;p style=font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;&gt;Amount reflects interest expense and associated financing fees relating to the bridge loans entered into under the prior credit agreement with U.S. Bank National Association (&amp;#x201C;U.S. Bank&amp;#x201D;) dated November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013 (with all related loan documents

			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Treasury Stock&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We record repurchases of our common stock
 $.01 par value (&amp;#x201C;Common Stock&amp;#x201D;)
 as treasury stock at cost.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We also record the subsequent retirement of these treasury shares at cost.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The excess of the cost of the shares retired over their par value is allocated between additional paid-in capital and retained earnings.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The amount recorded as a reduction of paid-in capital is based on such excess.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=margin-left:0%;margin-right:0%;&gt;

				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:04.16%;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;3.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Acquisitions&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Sin In A Tin&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On September&amp;nbsp;29
 2014
 we acquired the assets and intellectual property of a small boutique frozen desserts business
 Sin In A Tin&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:6.5pt;&gt;TM&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;
 for approximately $160
000 in cash. An additional amount of up to $0.5 million is payable to the seller in the form of an earn-out based on future net revenues attributable to Sin In A Tin&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:6.5pt;&gt;TM&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; products.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;At the time of acquisition
 the contingent consideration was recorded at $0.2 million based on the fair value assessment.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Additionally
 we recorded $0.1 million of identifiable intangible assets and $0.1 million of net tangible assets that were assumed as a part of this acquisition based on their estimated fair values
 and $0.2 million of residual goodwill.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Fresh Frozen Foods&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013
 we acquired substantially all of the assets
 properties and rights of Fresh Frozen Foods
 a branded frozen vegetable processor.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As consideration for the acquisition
 we assumed certain liabilities and obligations of Fresh Frozen Foods and paid an aggregate purchase price of $38.4 million in cash plus a working capital adjustment of $0.4 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;A portion of the purchase price was used to settle Fresh Frozen Foods&amp;#x2019; existing debt as of the closing of the transaction.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;An additional amount of up to $3.0 million could have been payable to Fresh Frozen Foods as contingent consideration in the form of an earn-out based on the achievement of specified fiscal 2014 performance objectives
 which were not met.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;At the time of acquisition
 the contingent consideration was recorded at $2.7 million based on the fair value assessment at acquisition.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Such contingent payment
 if any
 would be paid during the first quarter of fiscal 2015. Acquisition costs of $1.1 million were incurred during the year ended December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013 and are included within selling
 general and administrative expenses.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The amount of net revenues attributable to Fresh Frozen Foods included in the consolidated statements of operations since the acquisition date were $8.9 million in fiscal 2013.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We do not allocate certain selling
 general and administrative expenses and therefore
 it is impracticable for us to separately identify earnings of the acquired entity since acquisition&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.66%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.20%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:11.62%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.06%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Under the acquisition method of accounting
 the purchase price as shown in the table above is allocated to the tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their estimated fair values.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The excess purchase price over fair value of net assets acquired was recorded as goodwill.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The goodwill recorded as a result of the acquisition of Fresh Frozen Foods is expected to be deductible for tax purposes.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Identified intangible assets of $20.0 million consist of customer relationships and trade name.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The customer relationships are amortized using the straight-line method over the estimated useful life of twelve years.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We believe the acquired trade name has the continued ability to generate cash flows indefinitely
 and therefore the trade name has been determined to have an indefinite life.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill of $8.3 million represents the excess of the purchase price over the estimated fair value assigned to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed from Fresh Frozen Foods. In accordance with current accounting standards
 the goodwill is not amortized and will be tested for impairment annually in the fourth quarter of our fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;See Note 4 &amp;#x201C;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill
 Trademarks and Other Intangible Assets&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;#x201D; for additional information.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Based on Fresh Frozen Foods&amp;#x2019; financial performance for fiscal 2014
 we concluded the earn-out would not be paid.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Accordingly
 the liability for contingent consideration was adjusted to $0
 which resulted in a decrease in operating expenses of $2.7 million during the year ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;In fiscal 2015
 as a result of the product recall (see Note 2 &amp;#x201C;Product Recall&amp;#x201D;) &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;we concluded that the intangible asset related to the acquired customer relationships of Fresh Frozen Foods was fully impaired.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Accordingly
 the Company recorded an intangible asset impairment charge of $9.3 million.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Willamette Valley Fruit Company&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On May&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 we enhanced our berry purchase and freezing capabilities by acquiring the berry processing business of Willamette Valley Fruit Company
&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; one of the Pacific Northwest&amp;#x2019;s leading processors of high-quality berry products&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;
 for a cash purchase price of $9.3 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;A&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;n additional amount of up to $3.0 million may be payable to Willamette Valley Fruit Company as contingent consideration if certain performance thresholds are met during the seven-year period following the closing of the transaction.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Under the terms of the purchase agreement
 we acquired substantially all of the berry processing equipment assets
 including a new Individually Quick Frozen (&amp;#x201C;IQF&amp;#x201D;) tunnel
 and other intellectual property and inventory rights.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We also entered into leases of the land and buildings containing the purchased assets in connection with the transaction.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The amount of net revenues attributable to Willamette Valley Fruit Company included in the consolidated statements of operations since the acquisition date were $14.1 million in fiscal 2013.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We do not allocate certain selling
 general and administrative expenses and therefore
 it is impracticable for us to separately identify earnings of the acquired entity since acquisition.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;$&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:12.00%;;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size:10pt;text-align:right; nowrap=nowrap&gt;&lt;div style=float:left&gt;&lt;/div&gt;3

					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td colspan=2 valign=bottom style=width:13.24%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.76%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.24%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:12.00%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.10%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Under the acquisition method of accounting
 the purchase price as shown in the table above is allocated to the tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed based on their estimated fair values.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The excess purchase price over fair value of net assets acquired was recorded as goodwill.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The goodwill recorded as a result of the acquisition of Willamette Valley Fruit Company is expected to be deductible for tax purposes.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The estimated values of current liabilities were based upon their historical costs on the date of acquisition due to their short-term nature.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Identified intangible assets of $3.9 million consist of customer relationships and trade name.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The customer relationships are amortized using the straight-line method over the estimated useful life of ten years.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We believe the acquired trade name has the continued ability to generate cash flows indefinitely
 and therefore the trade name has been determined to have an indefinite life.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill of $3.1 million represents the excess of the purchase price over the estimated fair value assigned to tangible and identifiable intangible assets acquired and liabilities assumed from Willamette Valley Fruit Company. In accordance with current accounting standards
 the goodwill is not amortized and will be tested for impairment annually in the fourth quarter of our fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;See Note 4 &amp;#x201C;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Goodwill
 Trademarks and Other Intangible Assets&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;#x201D; for additional information.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;During fiscal 2015 and 2014
 we paid $0.2 million and $0.5 million
 respectively of the contingent consideration upon completion of certain thresholds achieved during such fiscal periods.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We also paid $0.8 million in fiscal 2014 for holdbacks upon expiration of certain indemnification and completion of post-acquisition obligations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;In fiscal 2015
 we increased our estimate of the total earn-out expected to be achieved
 which resulted in an increase in operating expenses of $0.2 million during the year ended December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;In fiscal 2014
 we reduced our estimate of the total earn-out expected to be achieved
 which resulted in a decrease in operating expenses of $0.3 million during the year ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As of December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015 and December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 the liability for contingent consideration was $1.6 million and $1.6 million
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Consolidated Pro Forma Financial Information&lt;/font&gt;

		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The following unaudited pro forma consolidated results of operations (in thousands
 except per share data) assumes the Willamette &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Valley Fruit Company&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; and Fresh Frozen Foods acquisitions occurred as of the beginning of the earliest period presented.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The unaudited pro forma results include estimates and assumptions regarding increased amortization of intangible assets related to the acquisitions
 increased interest expense related to debt acquired in order to fund the acquisitions and the related tax effects.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The pro forma results are not necessarily indicative of the actual results that would have occurred had the acquisition been completed as of the beginning of each of the periods presented

			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Acquisitions&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We account for acquisitions using the acquisition method of accounting.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The results of operations of our acquired businesses have been included in our consolidated results from their respective dates of acquisition.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On September&amp;nbsp;29
 2014
 we acquired the assets and intellectual property of a small boutique frozen desserts business
 Sin In A Tin&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:6.5pt;&gt;TM&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;
 for approximately $160
000 in cash. An additional amount of up to $0.5 million is payable to the seller in the form of an earn-out based on future net revenues attributable to Sin In A Tin&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:6.5pt;&gt;TM&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; products&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; (see Note 3 &amp;#x201C;Acquisitions&amp;#x201D;)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013
 we completed our acquisition of Fresh Frozen Foods
 LLC (&amp;#x201C;Fresh Frozen Foods&amp;#x201D;) for a cash purchase price of $38.4 million plus a working capital adjustment of $0.4 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;An additional amount of up to $3.0 million could have been payable to Fresh Frozen Foods as contingent consideration in the form of an earn-out based on&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; the achievement of specified fiscal 2014 performance objectives
 which were not met&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt; (see Note 3 &amp;#x201C;Acquisitions&amp;#x201D;).&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On May&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 we completed our acquisition of the berry processing business of Willamette Valley Fruit Company
 LLC (&amp;#x201C;Willamette Valley Fruit Company&amp;#x201D;) for a cash purchase price of $9.3 million.&amp;nbsp; An additional amount of up to $3.0 million may be payable to Willamette Valley Fruit Company as contingent consideration in the form of an earn-out if certain performance thresholds are met during the seven-year period following the closing of the transaction (see Note 3 &amp;#x201C;Acquisitions&amp;#x201D;).&lt;/font&gt;

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Purchase Agreements&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;In order to mitigate the risks of volatility in commodity markets to which we are exposed
 we have entered into forward purchase agreements with certain suppliers based on market prices
 forward price projections and expected usage levels.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Our purchase commitments for certain ingredients
 packaging materials and energy are generally less than 12 months.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Licensing&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We produce T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s&amp;#xAE; brand snacks
 Tato Skins&amp;#xAE; brand potato crisps and Boulder Canyon&amp;#xAE; Authentic Foods Rice and Bean snacks utilizing a sheeting and frying process that includes technology that we license from a third party.&amp;nbsp; Under the terms of this license agreement
 we have a royalty-bearing
 exclusive right license to use the technology in the United States
 Canada
 and Mexico until such time the parties mutually agree to terminate the agreement.&amp;nbsp; Even though the patents for this technology expired in December&amp;nbsp;2006
 in consideration for the use of this technology
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of products manufactured utilizing the technology until such termination date.&amp;nbsp; However
 should products substantially similar to Tato Skins&amp;#xAE;
 O&amp;#x2019;Boisies&amp;#xAE; and Pizzarias&amp;#xAE; become available for any reason in the marketplace by any manufacturer other than us and such availability results in a sales decline of 10% or more
 any royalty obligation for the respective products&amp;nbsp;shall cease.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s&amp;#xAE; brand snacks trademark from T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s. under a license agreement with a term expiring in December&amp;nbsp;2019.&amp;nbsp; Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of T.G.I. Friday&amp;#x2019;s&amp;#xAE; brand snack products and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Jamba&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Jamba Juice Company under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2035.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Jamba&amp;#xAE; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Nathan&amp;#x2019;s Famous&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Nathan&amp;#x2019;s Famous Corporation under a license agreement with a term expiring in 2031.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Nathan&amp;#x2019;s Famous&amp;#xAE; products
 and are required to achieve certain minimum sales levels by certain dates during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Vidalia&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Vidalia Brands
&amp;nbsp;Inc. under a license agreement with a term expiring January&amp;nbsp;2019.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Vidalia&amp;#xAE; brand products during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We license the Seattle&amp;#x2019;s Best Coffee&amp;#xAE; brand trademark from Seattle&amp;#x2019;s Best Coffee LLC under a license agreement with a term expiring November&amp;nbsp;2017
 which automatically extends for a five-year period upon meeting certain minimum sales targets.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Pursuant to the license agreement
 we are required to make royalty payments on sales of Seattle&amp;#x2019;s Best Coffee&amp;#xAE;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;brand products during the contract term.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Legal Proceedings&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We are periodically a party to various lawsuits arising in the ordinary course of business.&amp;nbsp; Management believes
 based on discussions with legal counsel
 that the resolution of any such lawsuits
 individually and in the aggregate
&amp;nbsp;will not have a material adverse effect on our financial position or results of operations.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;(see Note 13
 &amp;#x201C;Legal Proceedings&amp;#x201D;) &lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=margin-left:0%;margin-right:0%;&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;16.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Concentrations of Credit Risk&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The Company maintains amounts on account with financial institutions
 which at times may exceed federally insured limits. The Company has not experienced any losses on such accounts.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Our primary concentration of credit risk is related to certain trade accounts receivable.&amp;nbsp; In the normal course of business
 we extend unsecured credit to our customers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We investigate a customer&amp;#x2019;s credit worthiness before extending credit.&amp;nbsp; At December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015 and December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 three customers accounted for 28% and 39% of accounts receivable
 respectively.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=margin-left:0%;margin-right:0%;&gt;

  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Principles of Consolidation&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The consolidated financial statements include the accounts of Inventure Foods and all of its wholly owned subsidiaries.&amp;nbsp; All significant intercompany amounts and transactions have been eliminated.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Our fiscal year ends on the last Saturday occurring in the month of December&amp;nbsp;of each calendar year.&amp;nbsp; Accordingly
 the fiscal year end dates result in an additional week of results every five or six years.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Fiscal 2015 commenced December&amp;nbsp;28
 2014 and ended December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&amp;nbsp; Fiscal 2014 commenced December&amp;nbsp;29
 2013 and ended December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&amp;nbsp; Fiscal 2013 commenced December&amp;nbsp;30
 2012 ended December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013
 resulting in a 52-week fiscal year.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=margin-left:0%;margin-right:0%;&gt;

  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  

		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;8.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;&gt;Term Debt and Line of Credit&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;ABL Credit Facility&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On November&amp;nbsp;18
 2015
 the Company entered into a new five-year revolving credit agreement with Wells Fargo Bank
 National Association (&amp;#x201C;Wells Fargo&amp;#x201D;)
 as administrative agent
 and the other lenders party thereto (with all related loan documents
 and as amended from time to time
 the &amp;#x201C;ABL Credit Facility&amp;#x201D;)
 replacing our Prior Credit Facility.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;All commitments under the Prior Credit Facility were terminated and all outstanding borrowings thereunder were repaid effective November&amp;nbsp;18
 2015.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The remaining obligations of the Company and its subsidiaries under the Prior Credit Facility generally are limited to certain remaining contingent indemnification obligations.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The ABL Credit Facility provides for a five-year
 $50.0 million senior secured revolving credit facility.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The ABL Credit Facility also provides that
 under certain conditions
 we may increase the aggregate principal amount of loans outstanding thereunder by up to $10.0 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;On November&amp;nbsp;18
 2015
 we borrowed $21.9 million under the ABL Credit Facility.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;We used the initial borrowing under that facility
 together with the proceeds from the Term Loan Credit Facility (described below) to repay all outstanding borrowings under the Prior Credit Facility (consisting of $101.1 million)
 to pay accrued interest with respect to such loans
 and to fund the payment of certain fees and costs relating to the Credit Facilities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The ABL Credit Facility will mature
 and the commitments thereunder will terminate
 on November&amp;nbsp;17
 2020.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The Company and all of its subsidiaries are borrowers under the ABL Credit Facility.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Subject to certain exceptions
 the obligations under the ABL Credit Facility are secured by a lien on substantially all of the assets of the Company including: (i)&amp;nbsp;a perfected first priority pledge of all the equity interests of the Company
 and (ii)&amp;nbsp;a perfected first priority security interest in substantially all other tangible and intangible assets of the Company and its subsidiaries (including
 but not limited
 to accounts receivable
 inventory
 equipment
 general intangibles
 investment property
 real property
 intellectual property and the proceeds of the foregoing).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The obligations under the ABL Credit Facility are also guaranteed by each of the Company&amp;#x2019;s subsidiaries.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Availability of borrowings under the ABL Credit Facility is subject to
 among other things
 a borrowing base calculation based upon a valuation of our eligible accounts and eligible inventory (including eligible finished goods
 raw materials
 and by-products inventory)
 each multiplied by an applicable advance rate or limit
 and certain reserves and caps customary for financings of this type.&amp;nbsp; If at any time the aggregate amounts outstanding under the ABL Credit Facility exceed the borrowing base then in effect
 a prepayment of an amount sufficient to eliminate such excess is required to be made.&amp;nbsp; Availability of borrowings under the ABL Credit Facility is also subject to a bringdown of the representations and warranties in such Facility and the absence of any default thereunder (including any such default under our financial and other covenants in our Term Loan Credit Facility described below).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Voluntary prepayments of revolving loans under the ABL Credit Facility are permitted at any time
 in whole or in part
 without premium or penalty.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Borrowings under the ABL Credit Facility bear interest
 at the Company&amp;#x2019;s option
 at a base rate or LIBOR plus
 in each case
 an applicable margin.&amp;nbsp; LIBOR is reset at the beginning of each selected interest period based on the LIBOR rate then in effect; provided that
 if LIBOR is below zero
 then such rate will be equal to zero plus the applicable margin.&amp;nbsp; The base rate is a fluctuating interest rate equal to the highest of (i)&amp;nbsp;the federal funds effective rate from time to time plus 0.50%
 (ii)&amp;nbsp;LIBOR (after taking account of any applicable floor) applicable for an interest period of one month plus 1.00%
 and (iii)&amp;nbsp;the prime lending rate announced from time to time by Wells Fargo.&amp;nbsp; The applicable margin is subject to adjustment based on the Company&amp;#x2019;s Average Excess Availability (as defined in the ABL Credit Facility).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Additionally
 to maintain availability of funds under the ABL Credit Facility
 we pay a monthly commitment fee of 0.25-0.375%
 depending on the average ABL Credit Facility balance
 on the unused portion of the ABL Credit Facility.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Ongoing extensions of credit under the ABL Credit Facility are subject to customary conditions
 including sufficient availability under the borrowing base.&amp;nbsp; The ABL Credit Facility also contains covenants that require the Company to
 among other things
 periodically furnish financial and other information to the various lenders.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The ABL Credit Facility contains customary negative covenant and also requires the Company
 together with its subsidiaries
 to comply with a Fixed Charge Coverage Ratio (as defined in the ABL Credit Facility). The first Fixed Charge Coverage Ratio measurement period is the end of first quarter of fiscal 2016.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Events of default under the ABL Credit Facility include customary events such as a cross-default provision with respect to other material debt. As of December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015
 the Company is in compliance with all covenants of the ABL Credit Facility.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;We use the ABL Credit Facility
 in part
 to fund our seasonal working capital needs
 which are affected by
 among other things
 the growing cycles of the fruits and vegetables we process
 for capital expenditures and for other general corporate purposes. The vast majority of our fruit and vegetable inventories are produced during the harvesting and packing months of June&amp;nbsp;through September&amp;nbsp;and depleted through the remaining eight months. Accordingly
 our need to draw funds under the ABL Credit Facility fluctuates significantly during the year.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;As of December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015
 there was&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;$26.0 million outstanding under the ABL Credit Facility and the net availability thereunder was $23.1 million.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Term debt consisted of the following as of December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015 and December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 (in thousands):&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;

464

802
				&lt;/td&gt;

						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Equipment term loan B due monthly through September&amp;nbsp;2020 (c)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:02.58%;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 12pt;&gt;
						&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;

				&lt;/td&gt;

						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:03.74%;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.68%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:16.24%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:03.74%;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.68%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:16.22%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:2pt double #000000 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
				&lt;td valign=bottom style=width:01.46%;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt;&gt;
					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
						&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:1pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
				&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt;text-indent: -18pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;(a)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 9pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Term Loan Credit Facility&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Also on November&amp;nbsp;18
 2015 and concurrent with the execution of the ABL Credit Facility
&amp;nbsp;Inventure Foods and certain of its subsidiaries entered into a new five-year term loan credit agreement (the &amp;#x201C;Term Loan Credit Facility&amp;#x201D;)
 with BSP Agency
 LLC
 a Delaware limited liability company (&amp;#x201C;BSP&amp;#x201D;)
 as administrative agent
 and the other lenders party thereto.&amp;nbsp; The Term Loan Credit Facility provides for a $85.0 million senior secured term loan that matures on November&amp;nbsp;17
 2020.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Term Loan Credit Facility also provides that
 under certain conditions
 we may increase the aggregate principal amount of term loans outstanding thereunder by up to $25.0 million.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As noted above
 we used the proceeds of the Term Loan Credit Facility
 together with certain proceeds of the ABL Credit Facility
 to refinance the indebtedness under the Prior Credit Facility and to fund payment of certain fees and costs related to the Credit Facilities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Unlike amounts repaid under the ABL Credit Facility
 any amounts we repay under the Term Loan Credit Facility may not be reborrowed.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Term Loan Credit Facility also matures on November&amp;nbsp;17
 2020.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The Company and all of its subsidiaries are borrowers under the Term Loan Credit Facility.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Subject to certain exceptions
 the obligations under the Term Loan Credit Facility are secured by substantially all of the assets of the Company including: (i)&amp;nbsp;a perfected first priority pledge of all the equity interests of the Company
 and (ii)&amp;nbsp;a perfected first priority security interest in substantially all other tangible and intangible assets of the Company (including
 but not limited
 to accounts receivable
 inventory
 equipment
 general intangibles
 investment property
 real property
 intellectual property and the proceeds of the foregoing).&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Borrowings under the Term Loan Credit Facility bear interest
 at the Company&amp;#x2019;s option
 at a base rate or LIBOR plus
 in each case
 an applicable margin.&amp;nbsp; LIBOR is reset at the beginning of each selected interest period based on the LIBOR rate then in effect; provided that
 if LIBOR is below zero
 then such rate will be equal to zero plus the applicable margin.&amp;nbsp; The base rate is a fluctuating interest rate equal to the highest of (i)&amp;nbsp;the federal funds effective rate from time to time plus 0.50%
 (ii)&amp;nbsp;LIBOR (after taking account of any applicable floor) applicable for an interest period of one month plus 1.00%
 and (iii)&amp;nbsp;the prime lending rate announced by Wells Fargo.&amp;nbsp; The applicable margin is subject to adjustment based on the Company&amp;#x2019;s Total Leverage Ratio (as defined in the Term Loan Credit Facility).&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The Term Loan Credit Facility requires amortization in the form of quarterly scheduled principal payments of $212
500 per fiscal quarter from March&amp;nbsp;2016 to September&amp;nbsp;2020
 with the remaining balance due on the maturity date of November&amp;nbsp;17
 2020.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;In addition to the scheduled quarterly principal payments
 the Company is required to make mandatory principal payments out of Excess Cash Flow (as defined in the Term Loan Credit Facility)&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;As of December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015
 the amount outstanding under the Term Loan Credit Facility was $85.0 million and the interest rate payable was 8.0%.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Voluntary prepayments of amounts outstanding under the term loan are permitted in whole or in part
 in minimum amounts as set forth in the Term Loan Credit Facility
 with prior notice but without premium or penalty
 on or after November&amp;nbsp;18
 2016.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;The Term Loan Credit Facility also contains affirmative and negative covenants that require the Company to
 among other things
 periodically furnish financial and other information to the various lenders.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Term Loan Credit Facility contains customary negative covenants and also requires the Company
 together with its subsidiaries
 to comply with a Fixed Charge Coverage Ratio (as defined in the Term Loan Credit Facility) and a Total Leverage Ratio (as defined in the Term Loan Credit Facility). The first Fixed Charge Coverage Ratio and Total Leverage Ratio measurement period is the end of the first quarter of fiscal 2016.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;On March 9
 2016
 the Company entered into the Amendment with the lenders party thereto and BSP
 as the administrative agent.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The Amendment amends the Term Loan Credit Facility to defer the Company&amp;#x2019;s obligation to comply with the Total Leverage Ratio until the end of the third quarter of fiscal 2016.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Events of default under the Term Loan Credit Agreement include customary events such as a cross-default provision with respect to other material debt.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;As of December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015 the Company is in compliance with all covenants of the Term Loan Credit Agreement.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt;text-indent: -18pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;(b)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 9pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;U.S. Bank Debt&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;On November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013
 we entered into a $60.0&amp;nbsp;million senior secured term loan and a new $30.0 million senior secured revolving line of credit with a syndicate of lenders led by U.S. Bank
 pursuant to a Credit Agreement
 a Security Agreement and certain other customary ancillary agreements
 or the Prior Credit Facility.&amp;nbsp; To facilitate the Prior Credit Facility
 the Company and its wholly owned subsidiaries entered into a Letter Amendment Agreement
 dated as of November&amp;nbsp;8
 2013
 with U.S. Bank (the &amp;#x201C;Letter Amendment&amp;#x201D;).&amp;nbsp; The Letter Amendment reconciled the terms of the U.S. Bank Credit Facility with the terms of the Loan and Security Agreement and that certain Loan Agreement (term loan)
 dated as of November&amp;nbsp;30
 2006
 by and between the Company&amp;#x2019;s wholly owned subsidiary
 La Cometa Properties
&amp;nbsp;Inc.
 and U.S. Bank.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;All amounts outstanding under the Prior Credit Facility were repaid in November&amp;nbsp;2015 with proceeds from the ABL Credit Facility and the Term Loan Credit Facility.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt;text-indent: -18pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;(c)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 9pt 0pt 0pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:3pt;&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Equipment Loans&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;In August&amp;nbsp;2015
 we entered into an equipment term loan with Banc of America Leasing&amp;nbsp;&amp;amp; Capital LLC.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The loan will finance up to $4.0 million of new kettles and related equipment for our Goodyear
 Arizona facility.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;The equipment term loan accrues interest at a rate of 3.22% and is expected to be repaid over 60 recurring monthly payments commencing April&amp;nbsp;2016.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;In August&amp;nbsp;2014
 we entered into two separate equipment term loans with Banc of America Leasing&amp;nbsp;&amp;amp; Capital LLC; one for $2.6 million to finance equipment to be used at the Company&amp;#x2019;s Rader Farms facility
 and the other for $1.9 million to finance equipment to be used at Willamette Valley Fruit Company.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Both of these equipment term loans accrue interest at a rate of 2.35% and will be repaid over 60 recurring monthly payments commencing September&amp;nbsp;15
 2014.&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;&gt;Net Interest Expense&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;text-indent:36pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;
			&lt;font style=display:inline;font-size:10pt;&gt;Net interest expense consisted of the following for the fiscal years ended December&amp;nbsp;26
 2015
 December&amp;nbsp;27
 2014 and December&amp;nbsp;28
 2013 (in thousands):&lt;/font&gt;
		&lt;/p&gt;
		&lt;p style=margin:0pt;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 10pt;&gt;

					&lt;p style=margin:0pt;line-height:106.67%;font-family:Times New Roman,Times,serif;font-size: 1pt;&gt;
